.TH "polyglot\-python" "7" "" "Runtime Documentation" "Polyglot Devcontainers"
.SH NAME
polyglot\-python \- Python starter and maintenance workflow
.SH PURPOSE
This page explains the supported Python workflow in
polyglot\-devcontainers.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page when working in Python starters or Python proving paths.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
task init
task ci
uv sync \-\-frozen \-\-extra dev
uv lock \-\-upgrade
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
The repository now treats \f[CR]uv\f[R] and \f[CR]uv.lock\f[R] as the
first\-class Python path.
.PP
In maintained Python paths:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]pyproject.toml\f[R] describes intent
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]uv.lock\f[R] describes the resolved environment
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task init\f[R] uses \f[CR]uv sync \-\-frozen \-\-extra dev\f[R]
.PP
In the published \f[CR]python\-node\f[R] starter image:
.IP \(bu 2
the image already contains Python, Node, \f[CR]uv\f[R], \f[CR]pnpm\f[R],
and the scanner toolchain
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]task init\f[R] still installs the project\-local Python and Node
dependencies into the mounted workspace
.IP \(bu 2
this is expected because \f[CR].venv\f[R] and \f[CR]node_modules\f[R]
belong to the project contract, not the image base layer
.PP
Safe default workflow:
.IP "1." 3
open the container
.IP "2." 3
run \f[CR]task init\f[R]
.IP "3." 3
do the work
.IP "4." 3
run \f[CR]task ci\f[R]
.PP
Dependency\-oriented workflow:
.IP "1." 3
inspect \f[CR]task deps:inventory\f[R]
.IP "2." 3
inspect \f[CR]task deps:plan\f[R]
.IP "3." 3
inspect \f[CR]task deps:report\f[R]
.IP "4." 3
use \f[CR]task upgrade\f[R] only when the path supports it
.IP "5." 3
rerun \f[CR]task ci\f[R]
.SH OUTPUTS / ARTIFACTS
Python paths may write:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]pip\-audit.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gitleaks.sarif\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-inventory.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-plan.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.md\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]pypi\-upgrades.json\f[R]
.SH COMMON FAILURES
.IP \(bu 2
Editing dependencies without updating \f[CR]uv.lock\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Expecting \f[CR]task init\f[R] in a fresh starter workspace to skip
local dependency installation.
.IP \(bu 2
Using a loose \f[CR]pip install\f[R] flow in a maintained \f[CR]uv\f[R]
path.
.IP \(bu 2
Treating compatibility workflows as equal to the \f[CR]uv\-lock\f[R]
path.
.SH GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 2
Prefer \f[CR]uv\f[R] operations over ad hoc Python package commands.
.IP \(bu 2
Keep \f[CR]uv.lock\f[R] checked in and aligned with
\f[CR]pyproject.toml\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Use \f[CR]task ci\f[R] after dependency changes.
